# HUD in-world only

Monitor HUD bars and AR waypoint overlays are **session UI**, not launcher chrome.

## Rules

- Draw **only** when an active world session has a player (`PlayerManager.PlayerTransform` present, or the project’s `HudWorldSession.IsActive` gate).
- **Do not** show Heading / Marked / Station (or any Monitor bar) on the UMM launcher, main menu, or other non-world screens.
- **No mod version on the HUD.** Ship # is `info.json` / Mod Manager only.
- **`— Heading` must never appear** as menu filler. If heading is unknown, omit the chip or hide the whole HUD — do not paint a placeholder outside play.
- Same gate for **AR overlays** (`ArWaypointOverlay`) and hotkeys that only make sense in-world (e.g. park mark).

## Why

Players read `v… | — Heading` on the launcher as a bug. Heading exists only while you can look around in the world.

